{{Infobox song contest | name = Melodifestivalen | year = 1989 | theme = | logo = | final = 11 March 1989 | presenters = [[Yvonne Ryding|Yvonne Ryding Bergqvist]] and [[John Chrispinsson]] | winner = "[[En dag]]" by [[Tommy Nilsson]] | vote = Regional juries | host = | venue = [[Ericsson Globe|Globen]], [[Stockholm]] | entries = | interval = | opening = }}
'''[[Melodifestivalen]] 1989''' was the selection for the 29th song to represent [[Sweden]] at the [[Eurovision Song Contest]]. It was the 28th time that this system of picking a song had been used. 1,223 songs were submitted to [[Sveriges Television|SVT]] for the competition. The hostess, [[Yvonne Ryding]], was the [[Miss Universe 1984|1984 Miss Universe]]. The final was broadcast on [[SVT1]] and was surprisingly not broadcast on radio. The show was watched by 5,328,000 people.
