on]] |-style="background: #eeeeee;" | {{Hs|1996-12-04}}4 Dec 1996 | WP | {{Hs|Obst}}[[Michael Obst (composer)|Michael Obst]] | ''Solaris'' | the composer, after [[Solaris (novel)|the novel]] by [[Stanislaw Lem]] |-style="background: #eeeeee;" | {{Hs|1996-12-09}}9 Dec 1996 | WP | {{Hs|Kulenty}}[[Hanna Kulenty]] | {{Hs|Mother}}''The Mother of Black-Winged Dreams'' | Paul Goodwin |- | {{Hs|1997-04-14}}14 Apr 1997 | WP | {{Hs|Watkins}}[[Roderick Watkins]] | {{Hs|Juniper}}''The Juniper Tree'' | [[Patricia Debney]], after the folk tale by the [[Brothers Grimm]] |- | {{Hs|1998-04-19}}19 Apr 1998 | WP | {{Hs|Hosokawa}}[[Toshio Hosokawa]] | ''Vision of Lear'' | [[Tadashi Suzuki]], after his stage play ''The Tale of Lear'' |- | {{Hs|1998-04-21}}21 Apr 1998 | WP | {{Hs|Bhagwati}}[[Sandeep Bhagwati]] | ''Ramanujan'' | the composer, after the life of Indian mathematician [[Srinivasa Ramanujan]] (1887-1920) |- | {{Hs|1998-04-25}}25 Apr 1998 | WP | {{Hs|Muller-Wieland}}[[Jan Müller-Wieland]] | ''{{lang|de|Komödie ohne Titel}}'' | the composer, after the drama ''{{lang|es|[[Comedia sin título]]}}'' by [[Federico García Lorca]] |-style="background: #eeeeee;" | {{Hs|1999-04-19}}19 Apr 1999 | WP | {{Hs|Sotelo}}[[Mauricio Sotelo]] | ''De Amore'' | {{Interlanguage link multi|Peter Mussbach|de}} |- | {{Hs|2000-05-10}}10 May 2000 | WP | {{Hs|Czernowin}}[[Chaya Czernowin]] | ''Pnima ... ins Innere'' | |-style="background: #eeeeee;" | {{Hs|2002-04-27}}27 Apr 2002 | WP | {{Hs|Werner}}[[André Werner]] | ''Marlowe: Der Jude von Malta'' | the composer, after the play ''[[The Jew of Malta]]'' by [[Christopher Marlowe]] |- | {{Hs|2002-05-03}}3 May 2002 | WP | {{Hs|Stahnke}}[[Manfred Stahnke]] | ''Orpheus Kristall'' | Simone Homem de Mello |- | {{Hs|2004-05-12}}12 May 2004 | WP | {{Hs|Staud}}[[Johannes Maria Staud]] | ''Berenice'' | [[Durs Grünbein]], after [[Edgar Allan Poe]] |- | {{Hs|2004-05-25}}25 May 2004 | WP | {{Hs|Ferneyhough}}[[Brian Ferneyhough]] | ''[[Shadowtime (opera)|Shadowtime]]'' |